	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=186225><span id=Scholar>The Honorable epetrusic</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>96 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Woven spider silks are not the same as spider silks, nor can one be made into another as far as I know.&nbsp;&nbsp;The woven spider silks are required for at least the Kelethin druid newbie armor quest, probably other newbie quests as well.  I am not aware of any use for them beyond those quests (in particular, no tailoring recipes), and I would suspect that's their only purpose.  Regular spider silks are what you want for tailoring.<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
